# Pre-Implementation Analysis

## Purpose
Ensure implementation starts with enough context and a small plan.

## Rules
- Read existing code before editing.
- Identify whether the change is a feature, bug, refactor, docs update, or experiment.
- Define the smallest useful increment.
- Look for similar patterns in the project.
- Decide where code belongs before creating files.
- For experiments, decide what stays experimental and what becomes reusable.
- Do not implement broad architecture for hypothetical future needs.
- Do not continue if requirements imply committing secrets or real `.env` values.

## Baby Steps
- One small behavior at a time.
- Verify after each meaningful change.
- Keep commits focused when committing.
- Stop and re-plan if scope grows.
- Prefer a short written plan for anything touching multiple files.

## Analysis Checklist
- [ ] Similar code was reviewed.
- [ ] Target files and folders are clear.
- [ ] Test strategy is clear.
- [ ] Secret/config impact is clear.
- [ ] Documentation impact is clear.
- [ ] The next step is small enough to verify.

